Last week, Michael Vick, Purnell Peace, and Quanis Phillips pleaded innocent to dogfighting charges.
Tony Taylor, another defendant, changed his plea to guilty, implicating Vick as the scheme's financier.
The indictment revealed gruesome details of dog killings and fights across state lines.
Animal rights groups protested, urging awareness of the brutal world of dogfighting.
Vick's NFL career faces uncertainty as sponsors cut ties.
Despite legal battles, Vick's co-defendants cooperate with prosecutors.
The case continues to unfold, with Vick's future hanging in the balance amidst mounting evidence and public scrutiny.
